storyInfo: An argument has driven a rift between the sisters. On a day of misfortune for the Liberi, perhaps they will be willing to change for one another.

attributes.content: Trimounts, Columbia
I don't think there's anything else that needs changing.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Good work, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Just doing my job.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: All I did was provide the basic data model and do some testing.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You did all the framework and the content within.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: The Astrological Research Association forum is in one week.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: That hole in the skies over Trimounts must be tough to deal with.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I doubt it has much impact on our family. Our parents have never been the type to build castles in the sky.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Hm... Mother and Father have been in Trimounts for a while. I haven't had the chance to go see them with all the writing that I have to do.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Do you want to see them, Genne?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Nope. You're the only Urbica who doesn't make my head hurt.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What are you plans for this... research brief, I guess?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I'll release it for academic usage, free of charge, once I've presented it.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: The stars beyond the Trimounts hole seem to move according to a different set of rules, but that's just a tiny piece of sky. It doesn't encompass all stars.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: With our model, however, all researchers will have access to the rough coordinates of constellations under the two systems, and derive their patterns and relationships.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It'll make things more convenient for people studying the stars.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Sounds like something you would do alright.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Didn't you say that the stars in the hole have opened up new possibilities for astrology? You've finished what you came to Trimounts to do. How about you look into my fortune for today?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You're interested in this stuff again?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It's fun, isn't it? Come on, sis.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Alright...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Contemplates)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Mutters)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Raises astrolabe)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: The results seem different from before...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: 'Today is a day of misfortune for the Liberi.'
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: That's the message from the stars.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It used to be more specific. Weird...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Sounds unlucky... well, don't think about it too much. It was a casual question.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Not the first time you predicted big trouble for me, only for me to end up just fine. Let's not dwell on it.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Have you finished your breakfast? I'll get coffee.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Yeah. Thanks, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Here.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Astesia Urbica? I'm here to pick up your package.
attributes.name: Deliveryman

attributes.content: Here it is.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Got it. Just to confirm, this is the address, and the recipient is Mr. Francois Urbica, correct?
attributes.name: Deliveryman

attributes.content: Yes. Can you deliver it today?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Should be no problem. Same town, and you've paid the rush rate.
attributes.name: Deliveryman

attributes.content: Good, thank you.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You're welcome. Pleasure serving you.
attributes.name: Deliveryman

attributes.content: Have a nice day.
attributes.name: Deliveryman

attributes.content: A guest? That old Victorian woman next door?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Mrs. Evans? No, just the deliveryman.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: He came to pick up some documents that I'm sending to Father.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Sis?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Are you out of your mind?!
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What is it, Genne?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: How many times have I told you? Send anything to Mr. Urbica, and he'll put his name before yours!
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You give him too little credit.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Really? Then tell me, have you ever published an article under your name, and your name only?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: ...I just felt like something this important calls for review by a pair of expert eyes.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Fine, fine, let's say that's true.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You could have summarized your questions and sent them to him. Why did you have to send the entire draft?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Trust me, he'll lift the entire thing and present it himself at the ARA forum, at which point it'll cease having anything to do with you or me forever.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: It's all for the glory of the Urbicas. I don't see any problem with the head of the family presenting it...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well, I do!
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Why do you think I went to all that effort to run away from home? So I could live free, without him controlling me all the time!
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: And now you just handed months of our work over to him, just because you felt like you wanted his eyes on it?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: It's my research too. Did you even think about asking me before sending out my results?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I didn't thinkâ€”
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You didn't think? Someone as careful and thoughtful as you?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Trust me, Genne, you're worrying too much. It's not as bad as you think. We're an important family, and Father will only sign the family's name on something as important as this.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Plus, he's reviewed and even edited my past papers. He discussed with me the pros and cons of adding his name to the top, and I agreed.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Yes, I know that all too well. Nice flowery words like 'for your own good', promises that will never be kept, and you fall for it, just like that.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Watch your mouth, Elena!
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You know what? You sound just like he did when he'd scold me, Astesia.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I only wanted to put the best foot forward with this, Genne. Why don't you put your paranoia aside? Trust me, I'll take care of things.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You could never say no to him, and you expect me to trust that you can take care of things?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Enough. There's nothing more for us to talk about.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Where are you going?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Back to Rhine.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Genne...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: This is Genesis's communicator...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Do you need something, consultant?
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: Where is Rhine's employee housing?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Are you looking for someone in particular? I can reach them by phone here, whether they're home or at work.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: That'd be great. Can you get Elena Urbica of the Energy Section on the line for me, please?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: One moment...
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: You're looking for Elena Urbica, correct?
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: Yes. Is something the matter?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well... Researcher Urbica seems to have moved out of her apartment when she applied for external assignment.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: Records indicate she is not currently residing at Rhine.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: Did she come to work today?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Hm... could I verify your identity first?
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: Sure.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Visiting Bibliography Consultant, Astesia Urbica.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Hands over ID)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Everything seems to be in order. One moment while I look this up.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: I'm sorry, but Researcher Urbica hasn't tapped into any Rhine Lab facilities today.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: She hasn't been back to Rhine?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Seems that way.
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: She gets a bad feeling.
('Today is a day of misfortune for the Liberi.')
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Is there anything else you need?
attributes.name: Rhine Reception

attributes.content: No, thank you.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Stop scaring yourself. It'll be fine.)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (She's just off the grid for a minute because she doesn't have her communicator on her.)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Maybe she went out for a walk around Trimounts.)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (The police station is this way, isn't it?)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (I need to find her...)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Pol...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: She swallows the words before they come out.
She started thinking about it.
All the top astrologers are gathered here in Trimounts right now, her father foremost amongst them.
What will happen if the reporters learn that a rebellious daughter of his has gone missing?
They would undoubtedly jump on the story.
Nothing good could come of it, not for her family, her parents, or for her sister.
And so...
She passes by the police station.
(I'm sorry, Genne... I'm such a useless sister...)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: (Come on, Astesia, think...)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Watch out! Runaway car!
(Who should I go to?)
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Aaaaaaaaghhh!!!
Huh?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Are you okay? Are you hurt?
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Sorry, I got distracted.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Dur-nar...? What are you doing here?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I thought you looked familiar. Turns out it was you, Astesia.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Some kind of luck, almost getting hit by a car in the middle of the day.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Same goes for the driver. Probably a broken part somewhere. Only so long you can avoid hitting someone.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Is he alright?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: He finally got the car stopped, but flipped it over in the process.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Looks like he's okay, though. Just climbed out from the car. That's him talking on the phone right now.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Some luck. If Rhodes Island...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Oh yeah! I can look for Rhodes Island!
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Do you have a minute, Dur-nar?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Er... I guess so.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Can I ask something of you, or rather, of Rhodes Island?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Let's go to the Trimounts office. This isn't the best place to be talking.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Here, drink some water.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Thanks...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well, if you ask me, it sounds like a little sisterly argument and that's all.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: You don't understand. From what I divined today... she may be in trouble.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You're the one in trouble. You almost got hit by a car.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: I'm fine.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You sure can be stubborn... just like my sister.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Older or younger?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Younger sister, at least biologically. I came to Trimounts because she's doing business with the charlatâ€”I mean, astrologers.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: A lot of the reserves are on vacation anyway. I had a bit of time on my hands, so I decided to come here and help out.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: I see...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Do you get along well?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well enough, but sometimes she gets a little bossy, or does things for me without asking me first.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: You said she's your younger sister?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I said biologically. But she acts more like an older sister.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Thanks to her, business actually got better after my father left. Compare that to her vagabond older sister.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Don't say that. We're all grateful to you for teaching us how to survive. I still remember how you sent me flying with one swing of your sword.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I was new on the job then. When I saw you waving your blade around like a feather duster without actually striking... ah, no sense bringing that up.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: You want the Trimounts office to help you look for Astgenne, right?
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: There's a few scouts around who don't have anything to do right now. You can give them a list of places your sister is likely to go to. They'll be happy to help.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: We can do this quiet, if you don't want word getting out. I know them pretty well, and I can help you take care of things.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Thanks...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Don't mention it. Every family has its own challenges.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: I sent out the private messages. Let's go check the remaining places. Maybe we'll find something.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: A-Alright.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Don't worry, no one's gonna get hurt.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Astgenne sure can hide. We've searched most of the public areas, and didn't even catch a shadow.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: It's getting late. You should go home, and we can pick this back up tomorrow.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: I... I want to keep looking for a little longer.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It's almost midnight. Your divination only said today was unlucky, didn't it?
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Go home, have a hot meal, sleep well, and maybe things will get better tomorrow.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Let's go. I can walk you home if you want.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: No... thank you... sorry about taking up your day.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Don't mention it. I'll be going. Take care, and don't do anything stupid.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I'll come first thing in the morning. Nighty night.
attributes.name: Dur-nar

attributes.content: Astesia walks home alone. The stars are visible in the hole in the sky above Trimounts.
But she only has her eyes on the road ahead, as she navigates bend after bend.
As the clock strikes twelve, she rounds the last bend, and arrives at her rented apartment.
There, she sees a ball of feathers curled up in front of the door.
Sis, you're back...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I forgot my key...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Sis?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Astesia says nothing. She buries her face in her sister's chest, sobbing.
She can't keep her emotions in check, and she doesn't want her sister to see her face.
Astgenne knows that, and so she stands there, holding her sister in her arms, allowing the tears to soak through her clothes.
For a long time they stand there, until both of them have calmed down sufficiently, and Astesia takes out her key and opens the door.
The sisters sit side-by-side on the sofa in silence.
Finally, the older of the two speaks first.
Sorry, Genne... I was wrong...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I'm partly to blame too... I just exploded the moment you said you sent Father the paper, and I couldn't listen to anything else.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I know the sacrifices you made to get away from home. You don't want anything more to do with Father.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It's like stabbing you in the back. I didn't think it would go like this...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: It's normal to ask your mentors to review a paper, just like in grad school.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Look at me. I have a PhD, but I couldn't even keep my emotions in check. I call you hard-headed, but I'm the one who doesn't listen...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I... I made up my mind. I'll go and see Father tomorrow. It'll take some time for him to get through the draft, and he wouldn't be done so early. I'll convince him to give it back. We still have a chance.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Um... about that.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Actually, the package never made it to Mr. Urbica.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You remember the deliveryman, the Liberi? He came to apologize just as the sun was going down and refunded the delivery fee.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: He had a pretty bad day himself. HIs truck flipped on its side after picking up his morning packages.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Oh...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Since your package was urgent, he took a bicycle to deliver it while his coworkers dealt with the rest.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: It was raining when he passed through the business district and he fell into a pond, getting everything soaked.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: He was in tears when he came to apologize. I consoled him and sent him on his way.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You were right, sis. Today was a bad day for the Liberi...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: It's all in the past. Don't think any more about it.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Here, your terminal.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Thanks.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Bad habit I picked up studying in Trimounts.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: When I get mentally stuck or get into an argument, I just feel the urge to throw everything to one side.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I leave my communicator behind, separate myself from phone and email, and just take a walk around Trimounts.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Let time take care of any emotions I can't.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: And from every once in a while, I forget my key, like I did today, and have to wait at the dorm entrance for someone to let me in...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You didn't eat all day?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: No... I had no appetite when I left, and I was locked out when I came back.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What about the box?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I bought some ice cream as a make-up gift, but I didn't expect you to be looking for me all day, so it's melted.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Didn't you have any money on you? Don't starve yourself.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Not after I bought your gift.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I'm hungry...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I'll make something. Wait a while.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Okay...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I promise I won't just hand months of our work over to someone else.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Not even our father.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I believe you.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: My sister.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: One week later...
I looked through the draft of your presentation. No issues.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Did you memorize all the terms?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Yeah.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Good. You'll be able to fend off any old timers who try to grind you on terminology.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: But you said you were speaking in the afternoon? I didn't see your name on the schedule.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Remember Mrs. Evans, from next door?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: The old woman? What does she have to do with this?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: She's an authority on Victorian astrology. She was supposed to be giving a presentation this afternoon.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I convinced her to let me sub in for her.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Mm-hm.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Does that mean the space next to Mr. Urbica will be empty?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: No, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Er... why are you looking at me like that?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Don't tell me you want to...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Give Father a surprise? Let him know that his favorite daughter has gone bad like her sister?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Please, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You had this all planned, didn't you? That's why you didn't say anything about the Astrological Research Association. You were just waiting for me here.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Come.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: ...Do I have to?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Running away won't achieve anything, Genne. Here's your chance to take Father head-on.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Come, take off your goggles and equipment.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: And change your shirt and jacket.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Are you sure about this...?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: It's a practical joke. Your favorite thing.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Wait, since when did I become a practical joker?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Let your hair down. Now that's a good girl.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Sis... are you really sure about this...?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Just shut your mouth and hold the sword and astrolabe. I'll do your makeup.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Perfect.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Please, sis... there's got to be another way.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Sorry, Genne, the forum is about to start. There's no time.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Try speaking in my tone.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Sia... a-are you really really sure about this...?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Bah, no, I can't talk like that.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: That was perfect.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Would it really fool Mr. Urbica?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: You don't need to fool Father. You just need to fool everyone else.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Plus, I'm wearing your clothes. What are you gonna wear?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: The most formal outfit, of course.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: 'Starseeker.'
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Phew. So glad to be back in light clothes.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: How did it go?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: A bunch of stuff went over my head, but for the most part, it was pointless bickering over a bunch of papers...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I would have left if you weren't speaking.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What about Father?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Father, well...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: He's a good scholar.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: The others place tradition above everything else, but he's willing to admit the changes happening before him, telling the rest that knowledge needs regular development and updating.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: He scolded those old hard-heads like he was scolding us. He's consistent, at least.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: That doesn't mean he's not a giant jerk, just like Ferdinand.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What about Mother?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: She was glaring at everyone with her cold, statuesque eyes, as usual.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: They didn't say anything about your outfit?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: All they did was raise an eyebrow when they saw me. They didn't even so much as say, 'Hello, Astesia.'
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Maybe the game was up the moment they saw me.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Never mind that silly stuff.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Good speech. The two old Urbica hard-heads never brought up any objections, and you dispatched the other nitpickers with ease.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I hear you're already getting interviewed by the press?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Yeah, they just asked some pretty standard questions. But I also got questions from two foreign scholars.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: We exchanged contact information, and we may be able to work together to improve the model and promote its usage in academia.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: As for Mother and Father...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I'm sure they expressed their dissatisfaction with me in the sternest tone, staring straight ahead.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: They've always been like this. They've never changed.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: (Fake voice) 'Astesia needs to know her place in the family.'
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: They're obviously mad at you.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Haha, don't say that, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: What are you gonna do now?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: We'll stay in Trimounts for a while longer. We've been too busy to go sightseeing or shopping.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: There's still time left on this apartment lease.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I'll go back and report to Father once everything here is taken care of, and once things have cooled down a little.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I'll tell him that this was the fruit of me and my sister's labor, and that I won't let him put his name on it.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Finally, you've come around.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: What about you, Genne? Are you going back to Rhine? I hear your old mentor is back with a directorship.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: No way. Rumor has it he's even more cantankerous when bossing people around these days.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: But if I'm being honest, Director Clooney's current project is... intriguing.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: How could I not be interested in a form of energy that can send a building into the sky?
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: But that's not a good enough reason for me to go back to working under a man like him. No opportunity is worth that.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I've made up my mind. I have no regrets.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I'll follow your example, Genne.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: You're already my example.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Well, there are worse things than your sister complimenting you.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Let's eat out today.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Alright!
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: By the way...
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Yes?
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Give me a heads-up if you're going back home.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: I thought you didn't want to go back.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: I want Mr. Urbica to know that the two of us are a united front against him.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: Now that's exaggerating things a bit...
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Well, I won't go if you don't want me to.
attributes.name: Astgenne

attributes.content: That's not what I meant.
attributes.name: Astesia

attributes.content: Let's go together.
attributes.name: Astesia
